title: Texans no show early in 44-26 loss to Dolphins
text:
Texans no show early in 44-26 loss to Dolphins Miami runs away in first half to drop Houston to 2-5 on the season. Mandatory Credit: Andrew Innerarity-USA TODAY Sports (Photo: Andrew Innerarity, Andrew Innerarity-USA TODAY Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
MIAMI – By the time the Houston Texans decided to show up Sunday, the Miami Dolphins had already put them out of their misery. 
Miami had a 41-point lead, Dolphins quarterback Ryan Tannehill had yet to throw an incomplete pass and Miami had picked up more than 300 yards of offense—all by halftime. 
The Dolphins destroyed the Texans, 44-26, to drop Houston to 2-5 on the season. It’s the first time Miami has beaten the Texans in eight tries. 
Box Score: Houston Texans vs. Miami Dolphins 
“That was not a good performance,” Texans head coach Bill O’Brien said. “It’s terrible. It’s something I take full responsibility for.” 
It’s five losses this season O’Brien has taken the blame, and not much seems to change each week. 
Another stagnant offense that finally strung together drives when it didn’t matter.
